This is an edit to FeatureWheelShowState.ts that implements the B2 approach decided earlier. Let me parse what actually changed:

OLD CODE:
```
            // 退場 Out（盤面回歸+中間功能暗掉）：等全部轉動與效果（含 transfer）演完才播，一個 round 一次
            await this.PlayWheelExit();
        }
        finally
        {
            // 停留一下再收尾
            await Define.Wait( this.m_gameView, FeatureWheelShowState.STAY_DURATION );

            // 盤面效果收尾：停震動 + 還原 ZoomIn（await 還原完成，盤面回正後才續流程）。
            // 放 finally 確保即使上面拋例外也會停震動/還原盤面，不卡死畫面。
            await this.StopBoardEffect();
        }
```

NEW CODE:
```
            // 退場前停留一拍（讓玩家看清標記後的盤面）
            await Define.Wait( this.m_gameView, FeatureWheelShowState.STAY_DURATION );

            // 衝突2(B2)：盤面縮小(RESTORE_ZOOM) 與 退場 Out 並行——盤面回正的同時轉輪退場，
            // 與進場「放大(ZoomIn)+Active 同時」對稱。兩者作用對象不同（GameView transform vs BigWheel Spine），
            // 無共用 target，可安全並行。
            await Promise.all( [ this.StopBoardEffect(), this.PlayWheelExit() ] );
        }
        finally
        {
            // 安全網：例外路徑保證盤面還原（happy path 已並行還原）。
            // RestoreZoom 冪等——m_isZoomed 在還原完成才設 false，故 happy path resolve 後此處 no-op，不會縮兩次。
            await this.StopBoardEffect();
        }
```

The main shift is parallelizing board restoration and wheel exit using Promise.all instead of sequential execution. The pause duration now happens before this parallel operation, and the finally block becomes a safety net that leverages RestoreZoom's idempotent behavior—the m_isZoomed flag only resets after restoration completes, so the happy path won't double-shrink the board.
